Cell[TextData[{
 "will serve to assign identifying numbers to the eight nodal junctions: it \
is simply as a matter of style\[LongDash]and of no real \
consequence\[LongDash]that I have arranged for the numbers assigned to \
diametrically opposite nodes sum in every instance to 9. It will be assumed \
initially that a current J enters the circuit at the high-potental node #1, \
exits at the low-potential (grounded) diametric node #8. \n\n",
 StyleBox["PROBLEM", "Subsection",
  FontColor->RGBColor[0, 0, 1]],
 StyleBox[": ",
  FontColor->RGBColor[0, 0, 1]],
 StyleBox["Find (1) the current in every resistive edge) and (2) the \
potential differences between every pair of nodes",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontColor->RGBColor[0, 0, 1]],
 StyleBox[", given either the through-current J or the impressed potential V.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " \n\nThere are, we note,  a total of"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5257483828251553`*^9, 3.525748392417775*^9}, {
   3.525748863959969*^9, 3.5257489803985243`*^9}, {3.525749020580411*^9, 
   3.5257490286596413`*^9}, {3.525749067623064*^9, 3.525749089659972*^9}, {
   3.525749164577537*^9, 3.525749193940011*^9}, {3.5257492462898912`*^9, 
   3.525749299238226*^9}, {3.525749331693923*^9, 3.525749406921053*^9}, {
   3.5257494441325274`*^9, 3.525749447259555*^9}, {3.525749478242918*^9, 
   3.5257494887301197`*^9}, {3.5257496481735573`*^9, 3.525749664051216*^9}, {
   3.525749697200135*^9, 3.525749699912586*^9}, {3.526178485503599*^9, 
   3.526178555859747*^9}, {3.5261788257029343`*^9, 3.5261788584983053`*^9}, {
   3.5261788959058228`*^9, 3.526178953887735*^9}, 3.526218663007208*^9, {
   3.5262193390089817`*^9, 3.5262194032880898`*^9}}],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"1", "+", "2", "+", "3", "+", "4", "+", "5", "+", "6", "+", "7"}], 
  "\[Equal]", 
  RowBox[{"Binomial", "[", 
   RowBox[{"8", ",", "2"}], "]"}], "\[Equal]", "28"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5257495196327143`*^9, 3.525749530090127*^9}, {
  3.525749593373822*^9, 3.5257496079099293`*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData["True"], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.5257495318203697`*^9, 3.52574960932372*^9}]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "such nodal pairs, but those potential differences are all latent in the \
eight nodal potentials relative to ground.\n\nIf we proposed to approach the \
problem by textbook appeal to \n \n  \[Bullet] ",
 StyleBox["Kirchhoff's nodal rule",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " (conservation of charge);\n  \[Bullet] ",
 StyleBox["Kirchhoff's loop rule",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " (static ",
 StyleBox["E",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-fields are conservative: \[ContourIntegral]  ",
 StyleBox["E ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\[Bullet] ",
 StyleBox["ds",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " = 0);\n  \[Bullet] ",
 StyleBox["Ohm's Law",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n  \nwe would standardly begin by arbitrarily assigning directionality to \
the current flow through each resistor, which is to say: we would work from \
an arbitrarily ",
 StyleBox["directed graph",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ":  "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.525749686866991*^9, 3.5257496909331512`*^9}, {
  3.525749752741056*^9, 3.525749825465612*^9}, {3.5257499245695744`*^9, 
  3.5257499847311783`*^9}, {3.525750124256757*^9, 3.5257501912886744`*^9}, {
  3.525750230076388*^9, 3.525750354329805*^9}, {3.525750510769313*^9, 
  3.525750521514575*^9}, {3.525750697667439*^9, 3.525750738768527*^9}, {
  3.5257862896473093`*^9, 3.5257863065452957`*^9}, {3.525786398283573*^9, 
  3.5257864238352633`*^9}, {3.526179009753297*^9, 3.526179010712532*^9}, {
  3.526179073957939*^9, 3.526179087717977*^9}, {3.5261791532786818`*^9, 
  3.526179174018311*^9}}],

