Cell["\<\
REMARK: In the figure I have looked to physical intuition for my \
directionality assignments.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.525750385619957*^9, 3.52575038901198*^9}, {
  3.525750547285396*^9, 3.525750550156085*^9}, {3.52575058629626*^9, 
  3.5257506093543453`*^9}, {3.525831962233252*^9, 3.5258319693218737`*^9}}],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The textbook approach leads (because, according to Ohm, resistors are \
linear devices) to a readily soluable system of 2N simultaneous linear \
equations, but suffers from this defect: there is\[LongDash]except in the \
simplest cases\[LongDash]no \"most natural\" way to select N independent \
loops from the very large (how large?) set of all possible loops. Every such \
selection is, to some (typically very large) degree, arbitrary, and tends \
therefore to conceal (",
 StyleBox["i.e",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "., to fail to transparently reflect) the overall structure of the circuit. \
\n\nI will describe two alternative ways to approach such problems, both of \
which are free of the defect just mentioned:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5257882324348593`*^9, 3.525788279344715*^9}, {
  3.5257883185243673`*^9, 3.5257884027570667`*^9}, {3.525788440408922*^9, 
  3.525788509480134*^9}, {3.5257885775911093`*^9, 3.525788673058299*^9}, {
  3.52578870512956*^9, 3.5257887433676662`*^9}, {3.52578878605967*^9, 
  3.525788801717475*^9}, {3.525789176461224*^9, 3.525789178524992*^9}, {
  3.526178694263549*^9, 3.526178761824609*^9}}],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["VARIATIONAL METHOD", "Subsection",
  FontSize->12],
 ": Implementation of the claim that the physically realized branch currents \
are those which (subject always to the constraints implicit in Kirchhoff's \
nodal rule) ",
 StyleBox["minimize the rate of energy dissipation",
  FontVariations->{"Underline"->True}],
 ". "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5257888758071613`*^9, 3.525788882461133*^9}, {
   3.5257889747434387`*^9, 3.525788987696075*^9}, {3.525789049622387*^9, 
   3.52578916247478*^9}, 3.525789203967165*^9}],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["MONTE CARLO METHOD", "Subsection",
  FontSize->12],
 ": Exploits the discovery that the DC circuit problem is mathematically \
equivalent to a problem involving ",
 StyleBox["random walks of the circuit graph",
  FontVariations->{"Underline"->True}],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.525789246451025*^9, 3.525789259891696*^9}, {
  3.5257893128336773`*^9, 3.5257894195400333`*^9}}],

Cell["\<\
Both methods provide ways\[LongDash]complementary ways\[LongDash]to gain \
direct insight into DC circuit physics. The situation here\[LongDash]at least \
so far as concerns the Variational Method\[LongDash]will be somewhat \
reminiscent of that posed by problems in mechanics, where \"energetic \
considerations\" are often more informative (speak more immediately to \
physical intuition) than are the laboriously constructed explicit solutions \
of the equations of motion.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.525789484995576*^9, 3.525789552969667*^9}, {
   3.525789587382761*^9, 3.525789621286953*^9}, {3.5257896846712093`*^9, 
   3.525789841656086*^9}, {3.525789888488402*^9, 3.525789907397867*^9}, {
   3.5261792920384073`*^9, 3.526179302351453*^9}, {3.526179358340588*^9, 
   3.526179464547611*^9}, {3.526179518037271*^9, 3.5261795201009207`*^9}, 
   3.526218838428451*^9}],

Cell[BoxData[""], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.526219128553877*^9, 3.526219128826618*^9}}],

Cell[TextData[{
 "I will, in the present Notebook, illustrate those methods as they pertain \
only to the classic ",
 StyleBox["unit cubic circuit",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " (12 resistors, all of unit value), and will be content to execute certain \
constructions \"by hand.\" In a companion Notebook I will consider \
generalizations of the problem, and will be at pains to indicate how ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " can be commanded to \"automate\" those constructions."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.526219134247197*^9, 3.52621925301643*^9}, {
  3.526219438381504*^9, 3.526219607794722*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData["\[IndentingNewLine]"], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.525789951781176*^9}]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Use of SYMMETRY ARGUMENTS to solve the uniform cubic circuit problem\
\>", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.525789987070846*^9, 3.5257900683841953`*^9}, {
  3.526219645909237*^9, 3.526219716700564*^9}, {3.5262197652102957`*^9, 
  3.5262197719692707`*^9}}],

Cell["It is clear by inspection", "Text",
