in fact never linger.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.526314254651716*^9, 3.5263143052789803`*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData[""], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5263145018781548`*^9, 3.526314502061434*^9}}],

Cell["\<\
If, however, we have interest in long walks then that \"by hand\" procedure \
becomes excessively tedious; we need an automated procedure. This works, as I \
demonstrate by generation of a typical 10-step walk :\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.526314568898473*^9, 3.5263145827980843`*^9}, {
  3.526315448630278*^9, 3.526315451018619*^9}}],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"NestList", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"RandomChoice", "[", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"Sum", "[", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{
            "#", "\[LeftDoubleBracket]", "k", "\[RightDoubleBracket]"}], 
            SubscriptBox["T", "k"]}], ",", 
           RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{"k", ",", "1", ",", "8"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "\[Rule]", 
         RowBox[{"{", 
          RowBox[{
           SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "1"], ",", 
           SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "2"], ",", 
           SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "3"], ",", 
           SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "4"], ",", 
           SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "5"], ",", 
           SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "6"], ",", 
           SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "7"], ",", 
           SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "8"]}], "}"}]}], ",", "1"}], "]"}], 
      "\[LeftDoubleBracket]", "1", "\[RightDoubleBracket]"}], "&"}], ",", 
    SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "3"], ",", "10"}], "]"}], "//", 
  "TableForm"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.525985272304997*^9, 3.52598528618442*^9}, {
  3.525985402571088*^9, 3.525985418681034*^9}, {3.525985610734816*^9, 
  3.525985630310368*^9}, {3.526314544608953*^9, 3.52631455110609*^9}}],

