Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "Creation and variational DC analysis of a ",
 StyleBox["randomly constructed",
  FontVariations->{"Underline"->True}],
 " 8-node circuit"
}], "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5258805697642117`*^9, 3.5258806361946163`*^9}}],

Cell[TextData[{
 "There is, of course, nothing special\[LongDash]so far as concerns the \
essentials of the variational method\[LongDash]about the cubic array, which \
is distinguished from other (8-node) arrays only by its particular/defining \
set of connection relations. Nor, for that matter, are 8-node arrays \
distinguished from N-node arrays in any fundamental way: for the purposes of \
this discussion I look to 8-node arrays simply because they lead to \
expressions that fit comfortably onto the page.\n\nDiscussion of general\
\[LongDash]randomly constructed\[LongDash]arrays becomes worth the effort \
because it forces the invention of certain general graph-analytic procedures.\
\n\nREMARK: The following discussion might serve as a point of departure for \
development of a numerical approach to ",
 StyleBox["percolation theory", "Subsection"],
 ".  Drop increasingly many resistors onto (say) a 100 \[Times] 100 array of \
nodes, and watch the conductance, which will increase from 0 to a maximal \
value. It is to the statistics of such procedures that percolation theory \
speaks. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.525881278514426*^9, 3.525881282210328*^9}, {
  3.5258813165745783`*^9, 3.525881324148942*^9}, {3.525881356363474*^9, 
  3.525881371733337*^9}, {3.5258814184249496`*^9, 3.5258815002491703`*^9}, {
  3.525881535812969*^9, 3.5258818004232893`*^9}, {3.525881844924076*^9, 
  3.525882000179406*^9}, {3.525882058225616*^9, 3.525882202752803*^9}, {
  3.525883599624812*^9, 3.525883734684929*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<GraphUtilities`\>\"", "]"}], ";"}]], "Input"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"\[IndentingNewLine]", 
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{
   "Construction", " ", "of", " ", "random", " ", "adjacency", " ", 
    "matrices"}], "Subsubsection"]}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.525883855045611*^9, 3.525883886251882*^9}}],

