Cell["\<\
is operative. But circuit-theoretic transition matrices are typically \
asymmetric (i.e., refer to \"unbalanced walks\"), because\[LongDash]though \
\[DoubleStruckCapitalC] itself is invariably symmetric\[LongDash]the \
denominators in the respective columns of \[DoubleStruckCapitalT] are \
typically unequal.

\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.525918796589484*^9, 3.525918974576233*^9}, {
  3.5259190450670023`*^9, 3.5259190452483892`*^9}}],

