Cell["\<\
The asymptotic state typically \"blinks,\" though the state described by the \
leading eigenvector does approach (because it remains always equal to) a \
steady asymptote. The leading eigenvectors emerges generally as the average \
of the blinking vectors:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5260530716689672`*^9, 3.5260530864894133`*^9}, {
  3.526053277321168*^9, 3.526053318651561*^9}, {3.526053388018487*^9, 
  3.5260534810336123`*^9}}],

